body:
It seems the root of the cause is that you can unselect all networks, which makes for a strange case of no network monitored, so no tokens are selected; hence none are accessible.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47554641/229443312-47ba7b55-39e8-4621-8cdd-a7d57528da7e.png)
@benjthayer, this looks like the best would be to be simplified from the UX. With the current design, a quick fix is disabling the possibility of unchecking the last available enabled network. Disabling the possibility of unchecking the last network (e.g. arbitrum) will require the user to check another one to disable the "last one" (e.g. arbitrum) !?
